Davidia involucrata’s occurrence data for the whole of geographic distribution range were compiled from our extensive field survey (carried out within the area comprised between 26–32°N and 98–110°E), the Chinese Virtual Herbarium (CVH; 
http://www.cvh.org.cn/), and the Global Biodiversity Information Facility (GBIF; 
www.gbif.org/). Although many records from CVH did not specify latitude and longitude, we were able to geo-reference detailed locations, using only specimens with locations specified in the label information. In total, after removing duplicate records within each pixel (2.5 arc-min, 
ca. 5 km), we obtained 203 presence records.
